          "expanded": "Think about the difference between someone who's trying to be charming — calculating how to come across, working for the impression — and someone who's just genuinely interested and genuinely present. The second person is always more magnetic. You have access to that second quality. When you're actually engaged — actually interested, actually caring — there's something about your presence that makes the interaction feel more alive for everyone in it. The trick is that it only works when it's real.",
          "in_the_game": "When you're genuinely engaged at the table — actually interested in what's happening rather than performing engagement — your presence changes the energy of the game in ways other players feel but can't quite explain.",
