          "expanded": "Think about what happens when you walk into a room genuinely happy — not performing happiness, but actually feeling it. The room changes. People get a little lighter. Things feel a little more possible. You have that kind of effect when your inner state is genuinely clear and genuinely open. It's not something you do — it's something that happens when you're not blocking it. And when it flows freely, it's one of the most beautiful and most powerful things you carry.",
          "in_the_game": "When you're genuinely clear and genuinely present, your emotional quality at the table radiates something that other players feel and respond to — often without knowing why. That's a real form of influence.",
