          "header": "You build genuine connection through the quality of your own accountability — by being someone whose word means something, whose actions match their values, and who takes full responsibility rather than deflecting it.",
          "expanded": "The unity your purpose carries at this line is built on a specific foundation: your personal integrity. Not moralized, not performed — lived. The trust that makes genuine connection possible has to be earned through consistent demonstration that you mean what you say and take responsibility for what you do. Your fulfillment comes from those relationships where the trust was real because the integrity behind it was real — where people knew they could count on you not because you told them they could but because you consistently showed them they could.",
